    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-09T14:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-09T14:05:00-05:00" n="869"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d869">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.74/885: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-09T15:05:00-04:00"
                            >January 9, 1943—3:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–435. British Embassy here states that West Coast Telegraph Company in Chile is
                    only accepting messages to Axis and Axis-controlled countries including Vichy on
                    the same terms as All America.<note n="38" xml:id="d869fn38">All America Cables,
                        an affiliate of the International Telephone and Telegraph Company.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Department informally advised by representative of All America that it has
                    received a message from its Santiago manager reading as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Incorrect. West Coast accepts all classes of traffic for all points
                            including Axis and Axis-controlled countries. AAC accepts for none of
                            these points including Vichy France. Transradio accepts plain language
                            messages only to all these points except Vichy France to which they only
                            accept Chilean Govt traffic.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please advise Department at your earliest convenience what the exact situation is
                    with regard to this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
